<paragraphs>
    <title>Transformations of Sine and Cosine</title>
<p>
    For each of the following (vertical only) transformations of the sine or cosine function, find the amplitude and midline.
</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p workspace=".25in">
           <m>y = 2\sin(t) + 3</m>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace=".25in">
           <m>y = 4-3\cos(t)</m>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace=".25in">
           <m>y = \frac{3\sin(t)}{20}</m>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace=".25in">
           <m>y = \frac{5-2\sin(t)}{5}</m>
        </p>
    </li>

</ol>

